3459303","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/joepie91\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/joepie91\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/1663259?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/joepie91","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/joepie91\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/joepie91","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/joepie91\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE2NjMyNTk=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/joepie91\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/joepie91\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/joepie91\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"joepie91","type":"User","id":1663259,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/joepie91\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/joepie91\/orgs"}},{"index":2,"author_association":"NONE","body":"Some further experimentation results:\n\nWhen changing the following line in [the spinning cube demo](http:\/\/cryto.net\/~joepie91\/three-test\/test\/test.html)....\n\n``` javascript\nvar renderer = new THREE.WebGLRenderer();\n```\n\n... to ...\n\n``` javascript\nvar renderer = new THREE.WebGLRenderer({antialias: true});\n```\n\n... the bug completely and reproducibly disappears. It looks like it only manifests when `antialias` is set to `false`.\n\nA version of the spinning cube demo with anti-aliasing enabled (ie. not manifesting the bug) can be found [here](http:\/\/cryto.net\/~joepie91\/three-test\/test\/test_aa.html).\n\nEDIT: Obviously, I don't know whether the bug _really_ goes away or whether it just stops affecting that particular example. I'm not sure this observation explains the two oddball cases listed above.\n","created_at":"2015-02-09T06:50:45.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/6042#issuecomment-73464632","i